WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-GB

00:00:00.089 --> 00:00:03.929
Borussia Dortmund were 18th in the table and
under huge pressure to get a result against

00:00:03.929 --> 00:00:07.100
Hoffenheim. How did they fare on Friday night?

00:00:07.100 --> 00:00:13.440
Well in the end it was a 1-0 win thanks to
Ilkay Gundogan, it was a hugely important

00:00:13.440 --> 00:00:17.390
result. Jurgen Klopp and his men relieved
themselves of the red lantern - that is the

00:00:17.390 --> 00:00:22.300
German version of the wooden spoon - and climbed
all the way to 14th in the table. Dortmund

00:00:22.300 --> 00:00:27.689
once again had a good goal wrongly disallowed
but they also got lucky for a change, the

00:00:27.689 --> 00:00:34.260
referee not giving a penalty that looked to
be so.

00:00:34.260 --> 00:00:41.140
Gundogan had a particularly good game in the
number ten role and at the back it was the

00:00:41.140 --> 00:00:48.640
fab four reunited for the first time for the
start since the Champions League final in

00:00:48.640 --> 00:00:54.200
2013. We must continue to work for more victories
said a very relieved Jurgen Klopp and indeed

00:00:54.200 --> 00:00:58.361
they must. Two or three more wins from the
last few games will make sure Dortmund go

00:00:58.361 --> 00:01:01.199
into the winter break in a much more relaxed
state.

