00:01:14.959 --> 00:01:23.399
a hatrick from Choupo-Moting consigned Stuttgart
to the bottom of the table and pushed Schalke

00:01:23.399 --> 00:01:28.450
all the way up to joint-fourth. Another game
with a big x-factor was Bremen's trip to Eintracht

00:01:28.450 --> 00:01:35.869
Frankfurt. It was a suitably bonkers affair
without much in the way of defending, and

00:01:35.869 --> 00:01:41.490
Alex Meier set Frankfurt on their way with
a brace. Bayer Leverkusen are also fourth

00:01:41.490 --> 00:01:53.240
in the table with an identical record to Schalke
after a 1-0 defeat at Bayern on Saturday.

00:01:53.240 --> 00:01:58.469
Frank Ribery's 100th goal for Bayern was enough
to secure all three points against a very

00:01:58.469 --> 00:02:05.590
technically astute Bayer Leverkusen, who frustrated
the home team but didn't create much themselves.

00:02:05.590 --> 00:02:11.459
When somebody suggested that Alex Meier should
be part of the German national team two years

00:02:11.459 --> 00:02:16.921
ago, he just waved them away and said no,
I'm too old. But he is still only 31 and he

00:02:16.921 --> 00:02:23.790
is top of the Bundesliga goal scoring charts,
ahead of Lewandowski and Marco Reus with 10

00:02:23.790 --> 00:02:31.180
goals after 14 games. In ten years with Frankfurt
he has scored 34 times in 66 games, that's

00:02:31.180 --> 00:02:35.209
better than a goal every other game. He is
typically modest saying it doesn't really

00:02:35.209 --> 00:02:45.329
matter who scores. Is it inconceivable that
Alex Meier would get a call up for the German

00:02:45.329 --> 00:02:50.390
national team next year? I'm not so sure.
Joachim Low isn't exactly blessed with strikers

00:02:50.390 --> 00:02:55.959
up front and he could do a lot worse than
having a second look at the Fusbol god from

00:02:55.959 --> 00:02:57.650
Frankfurt.

00:02:57.650 --> 00:03:03.019
Markus Weinzierl's Augsburg were the first
domestic team to beat Bayern Munich last season

00:03:03.019 --> 00:03:07.060
and they have a chance to repeat that feat
on Saturday when they welcome their big neighbours.

00:03:07.060 --> 00:03:12.209
They are third in the table, that's the best
position this small club have ever been in.

00:03:12.209 --> 00:03:16.599
Augsburg don't yet see themselves as genuine
contenders for the Europa League or Champions

00:03:16.599 --> 00:03:21.849
